Thanks for the comment @jart. Sorry should have provided more info. The kokoro build is failing with `/tmpfs/tmp/bazel/external/io_bazel_rules_closure/closure/private/defs.bzl:27:16: The `set` constructor for depsets is deprecated and will be removed. Please use the `depset` constructor instead. You can temporarily enable the deprecated `set` constructor by passing the flag --incompatible_disallow_set_constructor=false`. 

But I just realized this is due to the "io_bazel_rules_closure" dependency in the PR branch is too old.

@ychfan do you mind do a rebase?
